title: Today in History: FEB 4, Rosa Parks is born
description:
Today in History

Today is Saturday, Feb. 4, the 35th day of 2023. There are 330 days left in the year. 

Today’s Highlight in History: 

On Feb. 4, 1783, Britain’s King George III proclaimed a formal cessation of hostilities in the American Revolutionary War…
author: The Associated Press

title: Democrat Border Policy: Let Business Hire Foreign Workers
description: Multiple Democrats used a Wednesday hearing to justify President Joe Biden's lax border by arguing CEOs are entitled to hire more foreign workers.
author: Neil Munro, Neil Munro

title: Federal agencies had intel that could have prevented Jan. 6 attack but they failed to act on it, committee investigator tells NBC
description: Tim Heaphy, investigative counsel for the Jan. 6 panel, told NBC News that the FBI, DHS, and other law enforcement agencies didn't adequately prepare.
author: esnodgrass@insider.com (Erin Snodgrass)

title: Trump's new label for Ron DeSantis, 'RINO globalist,' has roots in a far-right conspiracy theory about an insidious global network of powerful people
description: Trump has been calling the Florida governor names like "Ron DeSanctimonious." His latest move was to brand DeSantis a "Republican in name only."
author: insider@insider.com (Cheryl Teh)

title: Ron DeSantis has a 12-point lead over Donald Trump in a potential 2024 New Hampshire primary matchup: poll
description: In the UNH poll, a little under half (46%) of GOP voters felt Trump should run for president again, while roughly 50% thought he should forgo a bid.
author: insider@insider.com (John L. Dorman)

title: NBC News reports federal law enforcement 'could have prevented' Jan. 6 riot: 'Did not act on intelligence'
description: NBC aired a segment Wednesday that highlighted federal law enforcement agencies' failures in the lead up to the Jan. 6 Capitol riot that occurred in the final days of Trump's first term.
author: Joe Silverstein

title: South Dakota Republicans move to pass sweeping election security bills
description: South Dakota Republicans are advancing several bills in the state Legislature that they claim would significantly reform the state's voting systems.
author: Associated Press

title: Making good on pledges
description: Reps. Adam Schiff, Eric Swalwell, and Ilhan Omar, who were stripped of their committee assignments by House Speaker Kevin McCarthy.

title: South Carolina's Nikki Haley to launch 2024 presidential campaign, joining Trump in nomination hunt
description: Nikki Haley of South Carolina, who served as United Nations ambassador during former President Donald Trump’s administration, will soon declare her candidacy for president.
author: Paul Steinhauser | Fox News

title: Ilhan Omar’s committee removal was a long time coming
description: Her ouster from the Foreign Affairs committee isn't surprising, given the case her fellow Democrats previously made against her.
author: Noah Rothman

title: Top Jan. 6 investigator: FBI, others could have stopped Capitol mob had they acted on intel
description: The Jan. 6 committee concluded the FBI and other agencies could have averted the Capitol riot had they acted on intel, the chief investigator told NBC News.
author: Ken Dilanian and Ryan J. Reilly

title: Top GOP Strategist Rips Trump For Attacking Nikki Haley, DeSantis: 'Loser'
description: So far, Trump is the only notable candidate in the 2024 presidential election. He has recently taken some verbal shots at his potential contenders.
author: Anna Skinner

title: The Born Loser
description:
Nikki Haley is going to lose. She knows she’s going to lose. That doesn’t mean it won’t be fun to watch.

title: This governor is best positioned to fill the NeverTrump lane

title: House GOP embraces mainstream media after years of bashing ‘fake news’
description: House Republicans have begun to blitz the airwaves they previously shunned. Last Sunday four of the five traditional Sunday talk shows featured House Republicans, a stark contrast to recent years when weeks or months could go by without a single House Republi…
